{"metadata":{"title":"set(returnOnCancel:)","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"returnOnCancel"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO12TaskProtocolPAAE3set14returnOnCancelS2b_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO4TaskC","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or clears "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"text":"’s return-on-cancel flag. This is only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"meaningful for tasks run via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task\/set(returnOnCancel:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"returnOnCancel","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"returnOnCancel"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", then cancelling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable"},{"text":" will immediately cause it to return, as though the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"task’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" had called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_return_error_if_cancelled()"},{"text":" and then returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This allows you to create a cancellable wrapper around an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"uninterruptible function. The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true},{"text":" just needs to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"careful that it does not modify any externally-visible state after"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it has been cancelled. To do that, the thread should call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" again to (atomically) set"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return-on-cancel "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" before making externally-visible changes;"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if the task gets cancelled before the return-on-cancel flag could","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be changed, "},{"code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will indicate this by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"returning ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can disable and re-enable this flag multiple times if you wish."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the task’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is cancelled while return-on-cancel is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", then calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_set_return_on_cancel()"},{"text":" to set it ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"again will cause the task to be cancelled at that point.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the task’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable"},{"text":" is already cancelled before you call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread()``\/g_task_run_in_thread_sync()"},{"text":", then the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true},{"text":" will still be run (for consistency), but the task","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will also be completed right away."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/task\/set(returnoncancel:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Task\/TaskProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Task":{"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTask"},{"text":" represents and manages a cancellable ‘task’.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/task","title":"Task","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Task","kind":"identifier"}],"fragment